reviewerName: Low-Ranking Reviewer "tell it like it is"
reviewText: i'm used to japanese movies of this type so this movie didn't seem terrible to me.  but there was plenty here for the cinematic titanic crew to make fun of that's for sure, especially in one particular character.  they don't have a film-only option i don't think, but then again i didn't make it a point to look for that either.i only have two dvds from this crew(a handful from the rifftrax trio, and lots from mst3k), and both compare favorably to the best the others have to offer.  the film itself moves at a decent pace, is in color, and has a cute girl from both the east and west.  that's good enough for me.  the riffing was mostly good, with a few humorous mistakes made along the way by the team themselves.the other dvd i bought from them was "danger on tiki island", both here on amazon for $15 each(looks like i will have to continue buying their dvds off the official site since the others on amazon are at inflated prices).  both are funny and pretty even, and both contain extras of some type.  tiki has a brief behind the scenes documentary look, while insects has:*  1st 5 minutes of "the alien factor"*  4 minutes of "danger on tiki island"*  5 minutes of "east meets watts"(what a great title)*  2 1/2 minutes of the tiki docufinally, one odd/distracting thing about the titanic crew's live dvd's to me is the fact all 5 of them are facing the audience/camera as they riff.  this is slightly distracting cause i find myself looking at them to see who's gonna riff next or react, as opposed to watching the screen for the next riff.  but these are funny enough for repeat viewings and i got used to it pretty quick.  both dvd's highly recommended.  now it's off to grab a copy of "east meets watts"(did i mention that's a great title?)
summary: movie is ok, riffing is really good.

reviewText: This is a great example of the Cinematic Titanic series.  The movie is schlockey like we like them, and the jokes are awesome.  Thank goodness the team has not retired yet.  If you like MST3K movies, you'll love this.  I have read some reviews where people don't care for the way the crew is set along the sides of the movie, but that did not bother me.
